<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-20T12:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-20T12:45:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5485: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-20T12:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                        1928—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 3:43
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>138. General McCoy took oath of office as Chairman of the National Board
                            of Elections this morning before the Supreme Court.</p>
                        <p>[Paraphrase.] General McCoy and I hope to have the decree issued on March
                            21. [End paraphrase.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>